# Methodology

## 1. Purpose

This methodology explains how the vehicle digital forensic reconstruction was conducted from an E01 forensic image analyzed with Autopsy.

The objective was to correlate extracted vehicle artifacts and recovered media to reconstruct an eleven-run operation, identify repeated movement patterns, map actor/device relationships, and test whether the declared cargo narrative matched the vehicle’s internal telemetry.

## 2. Evidence Source

The original evidence source was an E01 forensic image. The image was analyzed using Autopsy to extract structured records, recovered media, and timeline artifacts.

The repository does not include the original E01 file. Only sanitized CSV extracts, redacted exhibits, and derived visuals should be uploaded for public demonstration.

## 3. Tooling

| Tool / source | Use |
|---|---|
| Autopsy | Primary forensic extraction and artifact review |
| CSV exports | Structured analysis of vehicle artifacts |
| Recovered images | Visual corroboration of routes, stops, receipts, and events |
| Python / spreadsheet tools | Data cleaning, correlation, and visual generation |
| Manual forensic review | Timeline validation and interpretation |

## 4. Artifact Categories Reviewed

| Artifact category | Forensic purpose |
